Weekly Marketing Report Octxls Cc legal Tom Below is a copy of the Weekly Report from October through October Please note a few changes from last weeks report The Potential Revenue Generating transaction count as well as the Potential Revenue from those transactions has changed to reflect new Nom Logic Pricing as discussed last week An amendment template has been created and will be sent to customers for discussion purposes at the appropriate time in the revisions process We will monitor customers who have received this template in the upcoming weekly reports Finally we have included a new table in the report which reflects our Counterparties Current Trading Agreement Status This will include a reporting of which companies have ISDA Agreements ENA Agreements Counterparty Agreements or No agreements in place which should give us a more accurate idea of where our hang ups will be in the legal process If you have any questions please let me know Thanks Forrest

Weekly Report Cc legal Tom Here is a quick update of the Weekly Report User Status Last week we had production users guest users and new guest user IDs were submitted We are currently of our Goal in terms of Potential Revenue Generating Transactions Website Visits CommodityLogic website visits were down slightly on Wednesday Oct and Thursday Oct from the previous Wed and Thurs However Website visits were slightly higher than average on Friday Oct Marketing Status We had meetings last week with Calpine Cargill AEP El Paso and Allegheny There are currently no meetings scheduled for this week Our next meeting is Nov with Bridgeline Legal Status No Change Below is a copy of the Report Please let me know if you have any questions Thanks Forrest Forrest Lane Analyst Commodity Logic
